# BM-SG Program: The P2-C Obstruction Map Formalization
This Lean 4 file formally isolates the parity paradox and the limits of the 
Green-Tao-Ziegler parameterization over the squarefree collision error E(n).

Conjecture P2-C aims to bound the L2-variance of the squarefree representation function.
-/

open scoped BigOperators
open Real

/-- The arithmetic representation function r_sq(n) counts collisions d * m = n 
    where both d, m are squarefree integers <= D, M. -/
def r_sq (n : ℕ) (D M : ℕ) : ℕ := sorry

/-- The principal collision mass (DC Peak) contributing to the continuous Eisenstein 
    spectrum and blocking classical large sieve limits mathematically. -/
def principal_mass (D M : ℕ) : ℝ := sorry

/-- The zero-mean structural fluctuation E(n), explicitly breaking the density barrier. -/
noncomputable def E (n D M : ℕ) : ℝ := (r_sq n D M : ℝ) - principal_mass D M

/--
The Parity Paradox (Route M): 
A rigorous proof that any strictly positive arithmetic sequence operator 
fails to achieve power-saving cancellation unless forced into a zero-mean fluctuation.
-/
theorem parity_paradox (D M : ℕ) : 
  ∑ n in Finset.Icc 1 (D * M), (r_sq n D M) > 0 := by
  sorry

/-- 
The Complexity Barrier (Route R / OMP Failure):
The Green-Tao-Ziegler Dense Model dimensionality k required to bound the U3 
norm of the quadratic nilsequence is intractable for effective L2 integration.
-/
